                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360509-name-849" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-849" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-849" type="surname" value="GREEN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-849" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES GREEN</persName>
                  </hi>. On the evening of the 9th of May I was in Bridge-lane—I received information, and saw the prisoner running before me with my handkerchief in his hand—I pursued him, and called "Stop thief"—I saw my handkerchief in St. Bride's church-yard—he passed round there, and could throw it into the church-yard.</p>
               <p>(<hi rend="italic">Property produced and sworn to</hi>.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I was in Bride-lane, and heard a cry of "Stop thief", and a young man passed me very quickly—there was a man with a sack of char<lb></lb>coal—I fell down, and as I got up this gentleman came and took me—I did not take the handkerchief—I had another handkerchief in my hand.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
