                  </hi>. I live in Bride-lane. I saw the prisoner, at about half-past six o'clock that evening, in company with another—he made an attempt, opposite my father's door, to pick the prosecutor's pocket—I fol<lb></lb>lowed him, and saw him take the handkerchief, and I saw him taken into custody.</p>
